"If you think the Internet has affected your life, Ethereum will have that same pervasive influence on our communications and our entire information infrastructure," says Joseph Lubin, who's the founder of the Brooklyn-based software-production studio&nbsp;ConsenSys. "It will impact every aspect of our existence."
ConsenSys, which employs 68 people in nine countries, is developing applications to run on this ambitious new computing platform.&nbsp;
